-- Philippines' San Miguel plans to bid for United Biscuits alone
-- 
-- Thu Sep 11, 2014 10:56PM EDT
-- None



MANILA, Sept 12 (Reuters) - San Miguel Corp <SMC.PS>, the Philippines' most diversified conglomerate, is planning to make a solo offer for British snacks maker United Biscuits <IPO-UNI.L>, its top official said on Friday.

"No need for partner," San Miguel President Ramon Ang said in a text message to Reuters when asked if the company was  joining forces with other firms in line with its plan to participate in the auction of the British snacks firm.